nd nach den Konturen einer Antifolterkultur, die auf die Zeugnisse der Überlebenden antworten könnte.  afunded by Zürcher Hochschule der Künste  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDetention of personszCubazGuantánamo Bay Naval Base. 0aPrisoners of warxAbuse ofzCubazGuantánamo Bay Naval Base. 0aPrisoners of warxCivil rightszCubazGuantánamo Bay Naval Base. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009xPrisoners and prisons, American. 4aFilm. 4aFolter-Kultur. 4aFolter. 4aGefangenenlager. 4aGefangenschaft. 4aGefängnis. 4aGewalt. 4aHaft. 4aHungerstreik. 4aIsolation. 4aKulturtheorie. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aKunst. 4aKörper. 4aSuizid. 4aWiderstand. 4aÄsthetik. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Violence in Society.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aArt.  aBody.  aCultural Studies.  aCultural Theory.  aFilm.  aHunger Strike.  aImprisonment.  aIsolation.  aLiability.  aPrison Camp.  aPrison.  aResistance.  aSuicide.  aTorture Culture.  aTorture.  aViolence.2 aZürcher Hochschule der Künsteefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2023z9783111024950oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839466810?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839466810423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839466810/original  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023  aZDB-23-TGPb2023